studyArms.name: Pembrolizumab Arm
studyArms.description: Pembrolizumab (MK-3475) 200 mg IV every 3-weeks (Q3W) for up to 35 administrations (approx. 2 years).

studyArms.name: Physicians’ Choice Arm
studyArms.description: Investigator’s choice of one of three regimens: Paclitaxel (80-100 mg/m2 on Days 1, 8, 15 of 28-day cycle), Docetaxel (75 mg/m2 Q3W), or Irinotecan (180 mg/m2 Q2W).

studyCohorts.name: Global Cohort
studyCohorts.characteristic: Approximately 600 subjects enrolled globally (including China during global enrollment period) without regard to GEP biomarker status.

studyCohorts.name: China Cohort
studyCohorts.characteristic: Approximately 120 Chinese subjects enrolled to meet local regulatory needs, including those from the China extension enrollment period.

arms.name: Pembrolizumab Arm
arms.description: Pembrolizumab (MK-3475) 200 mg IV every 3-weeks (Q3W) for up to 35 administrations (approx. 2 years).

arms.name: Physicians’ Choice Arm
arms.description: Investigator’s choice of one of three regimens: Paclitaxel (80-100 mg/m2 on Days 1, 8, 15 of 28-day cycle), Docetaxel (75 mg/m2 Q3W), or Irinotecan (180 mg/m2 Q2W).

cohorts.name: Global Cohort
cohorts.characteristic: Approximately 600 subjects enrolled globally (including China during global enrollment period) without regard to GEP biomarker status.

cohorts.name: China Cohort
cohorts.characteristic: Approximately 120 Chinese subjects enrolled to meet local regulatory needs, including those from the China extension enrollment period.

epochs.name: Screening
epochs.description: Up to 28 days prior to randomization; includes tumor sample evaluation for PD-L1 and GEP.

epochs.name: Initial Treatment Phase
epochs.description: Treatment with Pembrolizumab or Investigator's choice until PD, toxicity, or 35 doses of Pembrolizumab.

epochs.name: Second Course Phase
epochs.description: Retreatment with Pembrolizumab for up to 17 additional treatments (approx. 1 year) for eligible subjects who previously achieved CR or completed 2 years of treatment.

epochs.name: Safety Follow-up
epochs.description: 30 days after end of treatment for AE monitoring; 90 days for SAEs.

epochs.name: Survival Follow-up
epochs.description: Follow-up for overall survival until death, withdrawal of consent, or end of study.
